Exercise 3.1
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\series default
Suppose 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 has probability function 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{X}\left(k\right)=\left(1-\theta\right)\theta^{k-1},\,k=1,2,\ldots$
\end_inset

, for 
\begin_inset Formula $0\leq\theta\leq1$
\end_inset

 and that 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

 has density function 
\begin_inset Formula $f_{Y}\left(y\right)=2y,\,0\leq y\leq1$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
(a) Derive the probability generating function of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
(b) Derive the moment generating function of 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
(c) Let 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{X}=Y_{1}+Y_{2}+\ldots+Y_{X}$
\end_inset

 be the sum of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 i.i.d.
 random variables with the same distribution as 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

 in (b), and assume that 
\begin_inset Formula $Y_{1},Y_{2},\ldots,Y_{X}$
\end_inset

 are all independent of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 is distributed as in (a).
 Compute the characteristic function of 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{X}$
\end_inset

.
 
